Music star, Teni ‘Makanaki’ has tongue-lashed those, who according to her, want to dictate where she channels her money. The visibly irate singer via her Twitter handle, used swear words on these unknown persons. She also accused them of constituting to the problem bedeviling the society while demanding they fixed themselves.   Yinka Davies to parents: query children’s income     Nollywood loses another veteran actor     Actress Remi Surutu loses mum   “Selfish muhfuckers wanna dictate to me how to spend my money and who to help. You’re part of the problem we’re trying to fight. Fix yourself,” Teni tweeted. The “Billionaire” hit maker further warned persons devoid of love in their hearts to resist the urge of preaching to her. “I’m not blinded by religion either, I believe in God, and he is love. Don’t preach to me if you ain’t got love in your heart,” she added.